  <section id="visual">
    <h2>5. Visual/Graph for Dashboard</h2>
    <p>A Sankey diagram would be an ideal visual representation for a Flow dashboard. This diagram would illustrate the flow of energy and resources from more fundamental, first-principle concepts to more emergent domains. The width of the flows in the diagram would represent the quantity of energy or resources, while the direction would show how they cascade through different levels of emergence.</p>
    <p>The diagram would start with fundamental energy concepts on the left side, such as physical and chemical energies. As we move to the right, these would flow into more complex domains like biological and informational. Any inefficiencies or "leaks" in the fundamental levels would be visually represented by thinner flows to the more emergent domains, illustrating how defects in basic principles can have cascading effects on higher-level processes.</p>
    <p>This Sankey diagram would provide a clear, intuitive visualization of how optimizing flow at fundamental levels can lead to greater efficiency and effectiveness across all domains of life and work.</p>
